<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1600 GMT, March 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON -- British Prime Minister John Major said today that the
General Election would be held on May 1.
</P>
<P>
John Major made the statement after visiting the Queen at
Buckingham Palace where he asked for Parliament to be dissolved.
This will happen on April 8.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister said he was confident of winning a fifth
term for the Tories.
</P>
<P>
TIRANA -- The unrest lasting for two months took a pause on
Monday and long-awaited peace returned to Tirana after Albanian
government bodies and enterprises returned to work.
</P>
<P>
Central and local government organs throughout the country as
well as businesses began to run as normal today. The
reconciliation government issued the top command on Sunday night
announcing that those bodies will restore order from the local
time of eight a.m. (GMT 6:00 a.m.), Monday (March 17).
</P>
<P>
The peace, rare in the recent two months, went back to most
regions and no gunfire was heard in the capital Tirana. 
</P>
</TEXT>
