<HEADLINE> Tanzanian President Visits Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa arrived here today for talks with Zimbabwean President
Robert Mugabe which are expected, among other issues, to
concentrate on the Great Lakes crises.
</P>
<P>
Mkapa, who is accompanied by his Foreign Minister Jakaya
Kikwete, was met at the Harare international airport by Mugabe,
Foreign Minister Stan Mudenge and other Zimbabwean government
officials.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are expected to hold discussions on the Great
Lakes region crisis emanating from a civil war in Zaire involving
Tutsi groups from neighboring rwanda, who have lived in eastern
Zaire for several generations.
</P>
<P>
The talks are being held two days ahead of a meeting in
Nairobi of African leaders on the crises which will prepare for a
bigger meeting of the 17-member Organization of African Unity
(OAU) organ for conflict prevention, management and resolution to
be held in Togo on March 26 and 27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
