<HEADLINE> OIC to Call for Session on Jerusalem on March 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RABAT, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of Islamic
Conference (OIC) will call for a ministerial session of its
Al-Qods (Jerusalem) Committee to study the latest situation in
Jerusalem, following an Israeli decision to build a new Jewish
settlement in an Arab neighborhood of East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The OIC said in a communique that the session will examine
"the dangers which are threatening the holy city, particularly by
reason of the persistence of the Israeli government to construct
settlements... in application of its plan aimed at Judaizing the
holy city and denaturing its Arab-Islamic style."
</P>
<P>
The decision to hold the session was made by King Hassan II,
who is the president of OIC now, during his talks with Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak who visited Morocco last Friday and
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The OIC has 16 Arab and African member states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
