<HEADLINE> France Again Appeals for Support of UN Peace Plan for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- France today again appealed on all
the players involved in the crisis of Zaire to support the peace
plan of the United Nations special envoy for the Great Lakes
region, Mohamed Sahnoun, which calls for an immediate ceasefire.
</P>
<P>
"We persist in hoping that all the parties will end up
rallying themselves around the plan of Mr. Sahnoun," said French
Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
He said that France continued to support the approach of
Sahnoun "as pursuit of military confrontations will bring about
nothing but destruction."
</P>
<P>
Zairean rebels took the strategic city of Kisangani last
Saturday and are preparing to capture Lubumbashi, the capital of
the mineral-rich province of Shaba in southern Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman refused to comment on the health situation of
Zairean President Mobutu Sese Seko, who was hospitalized in Monaco
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
But he pointed out that "the health of President Mobutu is a
subject of supplementary preoccupation in the Zairean crisis."
</P>
<P>
He also refused to comment on a statement made by Belgian
Foreign Minister Erik Derijcke that there would not be a solution
for the war in Zaire without taking into account the role of the
rebel leader Laurent-Desire Kabila.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian minister said at the European Union foreign
ministers' informal session on Sunday that the "epoch of Mobutu
has revolved" and that "one cannot step back in time." 
</P>
</TEXT>
