<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Agrees to Reactivate Macro-financial Aid to Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- European Union finance ministers
approved on Monday the plan to pay out ECU 70 million(80 million
US dollars) in macro-financial assistance to Romania.
</P>
<P>
The aid is the second instalment of a loan decided upon in
January 1994. The first instalment of ECU 55 million(63 million
US dollars) was paid out in November 1995.
</P>
<P>
The re-activation of EU's macro-finance assistance to the
country follows the decision taken by the Romanian authorities, on
February 17, to adopt a stabilization and economic reform
program.
</P>
<P>
"The (EU Finance) Council noted with satisfaction the adoption
by the Romanian government of a new macro-economic stabilization
and structural reform program," the ministers said in a
statement after their one-day meeting in Brussels.
</P>
<P>
They also stressed the importance of a rapid implementation of
the long awaited structural reforms, notably in the state sector,
saying the EU was ready to assist Romania "at this critical
juncture". 
</P>
</TEXT>
