<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe, Zambia Seek Increasing Trade, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A conference to find ways of
increasing trade and investment between Zimbabwe and Zambia
opened here today with calls for renewed efforts to consolidate
existing relations.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the conference, chief executive of the Zimbabwe
National Chamber of Commerce (ZNCC) Wonder Maisiri said the local
chamber and Zambia Association of Chambers of Commerce and
Industry (ZACCI) wanted full backing from their respective
governments in creating a conducive business environment.
</P>
<P>
He said, ''we will continue to call upon our governments to
work toward the elimination of all tariff and non-tariff barriers
to trade in line with the resolutions set out under COMESA and
SADC regional grouping.''
</P>
<P>
Maisiri said Zimbabwe did not look at Zambia only as a market
of its products, but equally important as a possible source of
raw material inputs.
</P>
<P>
In the area of investment, he said there was need for
deliberate and concerted efforts by business people from both
countries to forge closer relationships and explore more
vigorously possible areas of cooperation, including cross border
investment initiatives and joint ventures. 
</P>
