<HEADLINE> 331,000 to Have Phone Lines in Addis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Some 331,000 Residents of
the capital will have access to telephone service in the next
four years with 83,000 others to get electric power supply, the
Addis Ababa City Council announced here.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency today, the Ethiopian
government has allocated over 661 million Birr (about 100 million
U.S. Dollars) for the installation of the new telephone lines.
</P>
<P>
The council said, in the past four years, fax, telex and
telephone lines were installed for over 17,000 clients in the
capital with an outlay of 11.3 million Birr (about 1.7 million
Dollars).
</P>
<P>
It said, the Ethiopian government on the other hand has
finalized plan preparations to supply electric power to 83,000
dwellers at a cost of 185 million Birr (about 28 million Dollars)
in the next five years.
</P>
<P>
Over 23,000 new clients were beneficiaries of electric power
in the past four years with government budget amounting to 28.7
million Birr (about 4.3 million Dollars) allocated to this end,
according to the council.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the City Council, along with entreprenuers and
associations, is preparing to construct 10,000 houses annually.
</P>
</TEXT>
