<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Approves 3,186 Investment Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Investment
Authority had by last December approved a total of 3,186 domestic
and foreign investment projects, with a combined capital of 22.3
billion Birr or about 3.3 billion U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
This will create employment for 169,846 people, said Tadesse
Haile, general manager of the authority in an interview today
with "Merewa", a magazine published by the Press and Information
Department of the Ministry of Information and Culture.
</P>
<P>
Haile disclosed that 1,610 of the projects were certified by
the authority while the remaining were given licenses by the
Regional Investment Offices, Ministry of Mining and Energy and
the National Bank.
</P>
<P>
The general manager said 541 projects, with a capital of 3.5
billion Birr (about 530 million U.S. Dollars) and employing
22,548 people, had already been put into effect up to June, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Some 524 projects creating job opportunities for 29,655 people
are in their implementation phase, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Of the total projects, 40 are owned by foreign investors, he
said, adding that seven of these, which cost 197.6 million Birr
(about 29.9 million U.S. Dollars), have already been implemented.
</P>
