<HEADLINE> 1 Dead, 6 Injured in Cameroun's Ethnic Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Skirmishes that erupted between
two villages in the Northwestern Province of Cameroun has left
one man dead and six others seriously wounded, local newspaper
reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The conflict, which erupted on February 8, 1997 between the Oku
people and Din people in the Oku and Noni subvisions, emanated
from a piece of land.
</P>
<P>
