<HEADLINE> Iran Invites Kuwaiti Amir to Islamic Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Ali
Akbar Velayati today delivered here an invitation to Kuwaiti Amir
Sheikh Jabel Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah to attend the 8th Islamic Summit
scheduled in Tehran in December.
</P>
<P>
Velayati arrived here from Oman today after delivering the
same invitation from Iranian President Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani
to Omani head of state Sultan Qaboos. He also delivered an
invitation to Saudi King Fahd in Riyadh Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He is currently on a tour to countries of the Gulf
region to extend invitations to Muslim heads of states and
governments from Rafsanjani for the summit of the Organization
of Islamic Conference, the Muslim world's largest body.
</P>
<P>
Velayati also held talks here with Kuwaiti acting Prime
Minister and Foreign Minister Sheikh Sabah Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah and
other senior officials on bilateral relations and matters of
common concern. 
</P>
</TEXT>
