<HEADLINE> UNITA MPs Arrive in Angolan Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-nine UNITA 's members of
parliament and two other would-be officials of the government of
national unity and reconciliation arrived here by plane today.
</P>
<P>
They flew here with 49 family members from Bailundo, the
headquarters of the National Union for the Total Independence of
Angola (UNITA) in central Angola on a special plane of the U.N.
verification mission.
</P>
<P>
The arrivals of the second group of UNITA members bring hope
to the establishment of the national unity government. Earlier on
February 13, 12 UNITA'S MPs and four officials-to-be had appeared
in the capital.
</P>
<P>
The delay of the arrivals by UNITA members in Luanda before
January 25, had dashed the hope of forming the unity government
which should have been set up on that date. 
</P>
</TEXT>
