<HEADLINE> Turkish President to Attend OIC Summit in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel is to attend the Organization of the Islamic Conference
(OIC) summit meeting scheduled for March 22-25 in Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Omer Akbel told a weekly press
briefing today that Demirel was expected to hold talks with heads
of state attending the summit on international and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
He added Demirel might also exchange views with his Iranian
counterpart Hashemi Rafsanjani over the unpleasant diplomatic
friction between the two countries over the past weeks.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, Demirel will meet Pakistani President and
other senior officials to discuss issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Demirel will also leave for Lahor to attend the ceremony
marking the 50th anniversary of Pakistan's independence and a
Turkish-Pakistan Business Council meeting on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Following the OIC summit, Demirel will pay an official
visit to Bangladesh on March 25-27, where he will attend
Bangladesh National Day celebrations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
