<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman on South China Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- China's normal operation within
its continental shelf and exclusive economic zone is
"indisputable," Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Cui Tiankai
said in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
In answer to a question about a Chinese ship involved in oil
exploration in the South China Sea, Cui said, "the policy of the
Chinese Government has not changed."
</P>
<P>
According to the Maritime Laws of the United Nations, the
spokesman said, China enjoys rights to its continental shelf and
exclusive economic zone.
</P>
<P>
The oil exploration is being carried out in the northern part
of the South China Sea, within the continent shelf and exclusive
economic zone claimed by China, he noted.
</P>
<P>
China's right to be in this area is indisputable, Cui
stressed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
