<HEADLINE> Holland Euro-Asia Flower Group Set Up in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Holland Euro-Asia Flower Group of
was officially established in Beijing today, marking the entry of
Holland's flower industry into the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
Holland Euro-Asia Flower Group is an organization that
comprises 14 flower and gardening companies in the Netherlands,
France and Belgium. It wants to introduce new technology,
expertise, and products to China for flower and vegetable planting
and management, said the president, Yang Bing, at today's
inaugural ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Holland Euro-Asia Flower Corporation, the core company of the
Group, is a multinational privately-owned company registered in
the Netherlands, mainly involving flower business.
</P>
<P>
In order to develop the flower market in China, the company
hosted the '96 China-Holland International Tulip and Flower Fair
in 14 Chinese cities from March through June of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Ministry of Agriculture said that China had
75,000 hectares in flowers in 1995, which had a value of four
billion yuan (about 481 million U.S. dollars) and were worth 67
million dollars in exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
