<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Science Lecture Collection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A collection of lectures by
Chinese scientists has been published to increase the public's
understanding of science.
</P>
<P>
A total of 134 lectures from among 200 noted scientists from
the Chinese Academy of Sciences and the Chinese Academy of
Engineering are collected in the three-volume publication,
covering the fields of energy, bio-engineering, space technology,
medicine, and the information super-highway.
</P>
<P>
"The scientists have explained profound scientific theories in
simple ways and have helped the public's understanding of the
latest developments in science and technology," said Qiu
Yongsheng, director of the Xinhua Publishing House, publisher of
the collection.
</P>
<P>
"I believe it will play a positive role in encouraging Chinese
to be more interested in science," Qiu said at a ceremony marking
the release of the collection in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The work was the idea of the China Association for Science and
Technology and the two academies last March. A total of 100,000
people in Beijing, Shanghai, Tianjin and ten other major cities
attended the lectures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
