<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two-Month Growth In China's Fixed Asset Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Investment in fixed assets in
China rose 58.9 billion yuan during the first two months of the
year, an increase of 18.1 percent over the corresponding 1996
period, the State Statistics Bureau says.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate is 11.1 percentage points higher than that for
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Real estate investment was up 11.8 percent to 12.8 billion
yuan. The growth was 16.4 percentage points lower than for the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
China increased investment in agriculture, energy, transport,
and telecommunications at the start of the year, the bureau said
in a report. It put 1.3 billion yuan into agriculture during the
January-February period, an increase of 151.4 percent over the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Fixed assets investment in the western parts of the country
reached 7.8 billion yuan, 37.8 percent more than during the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The bureau warned that there is still the threat of a renewed
construction boom and cautioned the government not to approve
construction projects that overlap.
</P>
<P>
China had 1,826 fixed assets investment projects during the
first two months, 686 more than for the same period last year,
with planned investment of 16.5 billion yuan, a growth of 126.5
percent over the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
