document. It aimed at developing cooperation, trust and
interaction for the sake of peace and security, not only between
the two states, but also in Europe, he said.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Rodionov and Portillo also exchanged views on
European security issues and Russian-NATO relations.
</P>
<P>
The British defense minister said NATO and Russia could join
hands in building a new European security order.
</P>
<P>
Portillo, who arrived in Moscow Monday, was on his second visit
to Russia in four months. 
