<HEADLINE> Chinese Communist Party Leader on Sino-Japanese Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee, says that the younger
generation of China and Japan should carry on the friendship
forged by the older generation of leaders of both countries.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the remarks today in talks with a delegation from the
Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) of Japan, led by Deputy
Secretary-General Oda Seiichi and composed of young parliamentary
members. Hu said that the young people of the two countries should
contribute to the establishment of long-term, healthy and stable
Sino-Japanese relations.
</P>
