<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethio-Djibouti Border Security Joint Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Ethio-Djibouti border
security joint committee began its sixth meeting Monday at
Nazret, some 90 kms away from Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here today, the three-day
meeting which is attended by officials of the two countries from
the ministries of defence and foreign affairs, police,
immigration, the administration for refugees and returnees
affairs, will discuss issues related to free movement of people
and goods and trans-border movement of nomads.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also deliberate on plans aiming at curbing
illegal trade including drug trafficking, contraband and trans-
border criminal acts, the reprot said.
</P>
<P>
The 5th border security meeting was held at Ali-Sabieh,
Djibouti last October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
