<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-18 13:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Reiterates Support to Palestine, Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Parliament Speaker Ali
Akbar Nateq-Nouri reiterated today Iran's support to the people
of Palestine and Lebanon in their struggle to "liberate" their
occupied lands.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with foreign reporters today, Nateq-Nouri said
Iran supports the people in Palestine and south Lebanon "within
the framework of the international laws and regulation."
</P>
<P>
"It is the responsibility of all nations to help the people in
Palestine and South Lebanon," he added.
</P>
<P>
But he did not specify what kind of support Iran is offering
to anti-Israeli organizations such as pro-Syrian Hezbollah, or
Party of God, and the Islamic Jihad.
</P>
<P>
However, he said that Iran will continue its opposition to the
Middle East peace process, which is in danger particularly after
the outbreak of Jewish settlement crisis.
</P>
<P>
Israeli government approved a plan on building a Jewish
settlement in Arab East Jerusalem late February, which sparked
widespread protest from the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
Nateq-Nouri said Iranian President Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani
stated earlier that Iran will continue to offer "all kinds of
support" to the Palestinian Intifada, or uprising.
</P>
<P>
"We rejected the Middle East peace process as defective from
the outset. It is a joint U.S.-Zionist move in a bid to serve
their own interests," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said "our interpretation of the essence of the peace
process came true just recently when the Israeli government
began to breach all previous agreements."
</P>
<P>
"We made it clear from the very beginning that it (the Middle
East peace process) is a game intended to deceive the people of
Arab world," he noted.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian parliament speaker said that Israel negotiated
with Syria but it refused to give back an inch of their land,
which refers to the Golan Heights the Jewish state seized during
the 1967 Middle East War.
</P>
<P>
Despite its opposition to the Middle East peace process, Iran
has openly declared that it is not going to do anything to disrupt
the peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
