<HEADLINE> Banned Sprinter Makes World Championship Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Australia's sprinter Dean
Capobianco, who was banned by te International Amateur Athletic
Federation (IAAF) for failing a drug test, was on Tuesday included
in Australia's world athletics championships team.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old Capobianco was suspended until May 27, 2000, by
the IAAF after an inquiry overturned an Athletics Australia
decision which had allowed him to compete at last year's Atlanta
Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Capobianco tested positive to the steroid Stanozolol at a grand
prix meeting at Hengelo, the Netherlands, on May 27 last year.
</P>
<P>
Capobianco was named in the team for the August world
championships in Athens in case of a successful challenge to the
adverse IAAF finding.  
</P>
</TEXT>
