<HEADLINE> CSA Opens First Commodity Inspection Service Center in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The March 14 opening of a
commodity inspection center in Guangzhou augurs increased foreign
trade between China and North America.
</P>
<P>
The CSA/CCIC Customer Service Center, jointly started by the
Canadian Standards Association (CSA) and China Commodity
Inspection Corporation (CCIC), is CSA's first branch in China.
</P>
<P>
CSA's commodity authentication, supported by the 1992 North
American Free Trade Agreement, serves as a passport both for
China's products throughout North America, and for American
products sent to China.
</P>
<P>
CCIC, China's commodity inspection agency for export and
import, began cooperation with CSA in 1986. Several hundred
electrical appliance products manufactured by more than 1,100
Chinese factories have obtained CSA's safety licensing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
