<HEADLINE> International Housing Products Exhibition Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A total of over 300 businesses
from eight countries today displayed their latest wares here at an
International Housing Products Exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises from Canada, the Republic of Korea, the United
States, Denmark, Japan, Australia, Germany and China have
participated in the exhibition, co-sponsored by the State Science
and Technology Commission, the Ministry of Construction, the
Ministry of Machine-Building Industry and the State Administration
of Building Materials Industry.
</P>
<P>
The products on display include new wall material, thermal
insulation material, waterproof material, drainage pipelines for
water supply, sanitary equipment, and decorative materials.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, vice-minister of construction
Ye Rutang noted that vigorous international cooperation on housing
products and technologies will effectively push forward the
country's "affordable housing project by the year 2000".
</P>
<P>
Ye said that the affordable housing project, launched in 1994,
has been attentive to expanding the application of new housing
technologies and products from both home and abroad by setting up
model affordable housing districts.
</P>
<P>
So far, some 26 provinces, autonomous regions and
municipalities directly under the central government have made
plans for building 98 model residential districts nationwide. And
17 districts are nearing completion with construction areas
totalling two million sq m.
</P>
<P>
The official expects another 20 model districts to be built by
the end of this year with construction space forecast at two
million sq m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
