<HEADLINE> Crime House Burnt Down by Mysterious Fire in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A mysterious fire burned down
Monday night a shack house on a beach in northern France in which
two brothers raped, beat up and strangled four girls in February,
Agence France-Presse (AFP) reported today.
</P>
<P>
"The house is no more. When the firefighters arrived, all were
burnt," AFP quoted Patrick Quetelart, the mayor of Dannes where
the murders took place, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Louis Jourdain and Jean-Michel Jourdain, two scrap
collectors who were previously jailed for similar crimes, abducted
with a truck Amelie, Peggy, Isabelle and Andrey during a carnival
festival in February near the small town on the English Channel.
</P>
<P>
The third Jourdain brother, Jean-Luc, his girlfriend and their
five children who also lived in the shack before have removed from
the house and are on welfare of the local government.
</P>
<P>
Police are now investigating the cause of the fire. 
</P>
