<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Six German Soldiers Arrested for Racist Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Six German soldiers were arrested
Monday for beating up non-Germans in an organized racist attack in
downtown Detmold, a town halfway between Cologne and Hamburg, said
reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Police said the six young men were among a group of 10 off-duty
conscripts, who hit and kicked two Turkish nationals with baseball
bats and held a knife to the throat of an Italian national. The
four others escaped when police raced to the scene.
</P>
<P>
The three non-Germans suffered bruises and minor injuries,
according to police.
</P>
<P>
The conscripts, who wore army uniforms and helmets, shouted
racist insults during the attack. Witnesses said the group first
asked people in a pedestrian precinct where they could find some
Turks to beat up. Police were immediately called by a passer-by.
</P>
<P>
The case has been reported to the German army and military
police were in efforts to identify the four runaways. It was
reported that the 10 soldiers have been since January served in
the 3rd Armoured Reconnaissance Battalion at Rommel Army Base in
Augustdorf, 15 kilometers from Detmold. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
