<HEADLINE> Northeast China to Hold International Trade Fair in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- A major international trade fair
is scheduled to be held in June 15-21 in Harbin, capital city of
Northeast China's Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The fair, the eighth already, has facilities to receive more
than 6,500 businessmen from home and abroad, said Ma Guoliang,
vice governor of Heilongjiang today at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
"The fair will adopt various forms of cooperation," Ma said,
adding, "Besides trade talks, the fair also comprises negotiation
for economic and technical cooperation and for cash or standard
barter trade."
</P>
<P>
Ma issued a welcome to businessmen worldwide to participate the
fair. Officials from over 30 embassies in China, including that of
Russia, Hungary, and Saudi Arabia, as well as representatives of
foreign companies, attended previous conferences.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang, which shares a 3,000-km border with Russia, is
the major continental route for Asia and the Pacific regions to
reach Russia and Europe. The province is rich in oil, coal and
forests, and is China's major grain production area. 
</P>
