<HEADLINE> Information-Sharing Network Goes On-Line in Xiamen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- An internet service provider,
Xiamennet, has started business here today in this coastal city of
Xiamen, east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Li Zhenqun, director of Xiamen City Bureau of Posts and
Telecommunications, told reporters that the establishment of the
local information-sharing system could help subscribers surf the
Internet more quickly and at lower cost compared with the previous
rates via Chinanet.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the project will also make it possible for
clients to share information on local enterprises and government
departments, said the director.
</P>
<P>
According to Li, more than 800 enterprises and individuals in
the city have subscribed to the Internet so far.
</P>
<P>
Local government officials have called on people from all walks
of life to become clients of the newly-established service
network, so as to advance the city's economic construction. 
</P>
