<HEADLINE> China Patent Office to Import Information System From Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Patent Office of China has
signed a contract to import a 29-million-deutsche-marks
information system from Germany.
</P>
<P>
Siemens Nixdorf Information System AG, a computer arm of
Siemens AG, will join hands with another German company to help
the patent office set up a complete patent-searching system,
equipped with complete application platform and software.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 working stations will be built nationwide,
expected to shorten the time to perform a patent search from the
current eight weeks to less than two days.
</P>
<P>
The Patent Office of China is now in charge of nine million
registered patents, and receives 100,000 applications daily.
</P>
<P>
Introduction of the advanced system will help China improve
intellectual property protection, and promote cooperation with
foreign corresponding organizations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
