<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Calls for Cease-fire With Muslim Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Philippine government chief peace
negotiator Fortunato Abat today called for a general cease-fire
agreement between the military and the Moro Islamic Liberation
Front (MILF).
</P>
<P>
Abat made the call over a local radio following the resumption
of hostilities between the military and the MILF in Buldon in the
southern province of Maguindanao.
</P>
<P>
"Instead of blaming each other as to who first violated local
cease-fires in certain areas in Maguindanao, why don't we talk on
the general cessation of hostilities first," Abat said.
</P>
<P>
Abat also suggested that a subcommittee meeting be held
immediately before the scheduled third round of low-level talks in
April to include the general cessation matter in the proposed
agendas of both panels.
</P>
<P>
At least three government soldiers were killed in mortar
attacks launched by MILF rebels over the weekend against a
military detachment in Buldon.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Al Haj Murad, MILF vice-chairman for military
affairs, said a teacher and 10 students of a school inside Camp
Abubakar, the MILF's biggest camp, were killed and one was wounded
when the military shelled the school building.
</P>
<P>
Murad said they are waiting for appropriate actions from the
government to address properly the latest clashes in Buldon.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine government and the MILF signed a local
cease-fire agreement last month after a week of fighting in Buldon
claimed more than 50 lives.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
