<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Chosen to Form APEC Research Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has been chosen from 18
members of the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) to set up
APEC's center for technology foresight, according to a Thai
national science agency.
</P>
<P>
The center will conduct research on the development, transfer
and envisagement of new technologies that will be used in APEC
members, according to Thailand's National Science and Technology
Development Agency (NSTDA).
</P>
<P>
Each APEC member could propose their projects to the center for
research and development and the results will be exchanged between
APEC members, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand will receive 5 million baht (200,000 U.S. dollars)
from APEC in the next two years to build such a center, while the
Thai government will offer 17 million baht (680,000 dollars) to
assist the center in the first year.
</P>
<P>
The center, which is expected to operate officially next year,
will also receive financial support from users. The initial
research topics of the center will include computer crime and
retail trade technology.
</P>
<P>
There will be five to ten experts working at the center,
including some from Australia, Japan and Canada, but some will not
stay in Thailand as they work with other experts through computer
network, the agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
