<HEADLINE> Utah's Karl Malone Named NBA Player of The Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Karl Malone of the Utah Jazz was
named the NBA Player of the Week for games played from Monday,
March 10, through Sunday, March 16.
</P>
<P>
Malone led Utah to a 3-1 record in four road games as the Jazz
increased its lead in the Midwest Division to five games over
Houston Rockets.
</P>
<P>
He averaged a league-leading 30.3 points and added 10 rebounds
per game while shooting 81.3 percent from the free throw line in
38.3 minutes per game.
</P>
<P>
Malone has now scored 25,131 career points and needs just 62
more points to pass Hall of Famer Jerry West and move into 10th
place on the NBA's all-time scoring list.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for NBA Player of the Week were Denver's
LaPhonso Ellis, Golden States' Latrell, Miami's Isaac Austin and
Tim Hardaway, Orlando's Anfernee Hardaway, Philadelphia's Allen
Iverson, Portland's Rasheed Wallace and Toront's Marcus Camby and
Damon Stoudamire. 
