<HEADLINE> Election-related Violence Complaints in Sri Lanka Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Police Election
Secretariat announced today that it has received 1,592 complaints
of election-related violence so far from the seven provinces where
local government elections are to be held on March 21.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the secretariat said that this was an increase
of 111 from Monday's total number of complaints made by the
political parties contesting the polls.
</P>
<P>
Giving a breakdown of the complaints, he said the main
opposition United National Party has made 702 complaints followed
by the ruling People's Alliance 641.
</P>
<P>
He said that over 30,000 police officers will be deployed for
the election duty.
</P>
<P>
A special police unit will do its utmost to ensure the security
of voters and prevent any violation of the election law in the
coming days, he added.  
