<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Decline on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed on
the Singapore market while the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index continued to decline, falling by 10.94 points to finish at
2,124.29 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume was thin at 184.51 million units, worth
401.88 million Singapore dollars (about 283.01 million US
dollars). Declines led advances by 169 to 167, while 270 other
counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
MBF Holdings was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 7.57 million units. It was followed by MBF Land which
had 6.08 million shares traded. FACB was next with 5.29 million of
shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
NBT led the gainers of the day as it rose by 75 cents to finish
at 9.9 Singapore dollars. Singapore Land and Van Der Hurst
increased by 15 cents each to end at 7.9 and 5.35 dollars
respectively. Golden Plus was 14 cents higher at 3.26 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, GE Life was the biggest loser of the day as it
declined by 60 cents to close at 23.5 dollars. City Development
fell by 50 cents to 12.7 Singapore dollars, while the Development
Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign and the Singapore Press Holdings
(SPH) Foreign dropped by 40 cents each to end at 17.6 and 26.3
Singapore dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
