<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets NZ Defense Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian said here today that China attaches importance to
developing its relations with New Zealand and other South Pacific
countries.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also Vice-Chairman of the Central Military Commission and
State Councillor, made the remarks at a meeting with New Zealand
Defense Secretary Jerald Hensley in the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
Chi extended a welcome to Hensley and described him as an "old
friend". His visit, Chi said, would help enhance the friendship
and mutual understanding between the two peoples and the two armed
forces. He also believed Hensley's ongoing visit would add a new
chapter to the Sino-NZ military exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Hensley is the first senior NZ military officer visiting China
in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The promotion of China's relations with NZ and other South
Pacific countries benefits not only China and NZ but also promotes
peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The NZ guest arrived here Sunday at the invitation of Chinese
Defense Ministry. Gui Fulin, deputy chief of the general staff of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army, held talks Monday with
Hensley on the regional situation and relations between the armed
forces in China and New Zealand. 
</P>
