<HEADLINE> Ramos Marks Birthday by Donating Blood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today marked his 69th birthday by donating 250 cc of blood to the
Philippine National Red Cross.
</P>
<P>
The new donation brought to three gallons the blood Ramos has
"shed" for a good cause since he started his annual donation of
blood as a young military officer way back in 1957.
</P>
<P>
Before blood was extracted from Ramos, the Red Cross asked
permission from Dr. Raul Fores, the president's personal physician
who headed the surgical team that operated on Ramos to remove a
blockage in his right carotid artery last December 23.
</P>
<P>
Rosal, head of the Red Cross blood donation program, said they
had to be "doubly sure" that the president could donate blood
without any adverse effect on his health, considering his recent
operation.
</P>
<P>
Ramos was in high spirits as the fluid was released from his
body, even jokingly telling Rosal and other Red Cross staffers to
check if what they were getting "was not red wine."  
