-- At the age of 66, former U.S. secretary of state James Baker
accepted on Monday an extremely difficult mission: be the personal
envoy of the U.N. secretary general for West Sahara to "restart
the peace process on track." The United Nations has vainly tried
to organize a referendum of self-determination in this former
Spanish colony rich with phosphates, whose sovereignty is disputed
between Morocco and Algeria-supported Front Polisario.
</P>
