</P>
<P>
-- In response to the wishes of the country's family movements,
French Prime Minister Alain Juppe announced on Monday a series of
measures to help French families, including providing a 1 billion
franc (200 million U.S. dollar) package of family allowances to help
adolescents of 18 years old living in families with more than three
children from January 1, 1998.
</P>
<P>
-- In France, 7.5 percent of the staff of the armed forces are
women, which is among the highest in European countries. The
percentage of women serving in the country's air force is 11
percent, higher than in other military forces.
</P>
<P>
-- While Europe's auto industry is suffering from over-production
as is shown by the on-going crisis of the Renault auto group, the
Japanese automaker Toyota is considering to open a new assembly
plant with an annual production capacity of 200,000 cars in France
with a 1.6 billion U.S. dollar investment. The decision will be
announced on May 10.  
</P>
