<HEADLINE> Sudanese Refugees in Uganda Return Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of Sudanese refugees
departed yesterday from their camps in northwestern Uganda for
home in the wake of defeat of West Nile Bank Front (WNBF).
</P>
<P>
The returning refugees line up to a 15-kilometer rank from
Koboko in northwestern Uganda to the border town of Kaya in
southern Sudan. The refugees returned with their goats, dogs and
properties.
</P>
<P>
''We are very happy to return to be back in our country. We
have suffered enough at the hands of Ugandan rebels,'' Julius
Abe, a 27-year old refugee told the New Vision yesterday in Kaya.
</P>
<P>
He said he will prepare a shelter for his family.
</P>
<P>
The WNBF is a Sudan and Zaire based rebel group acting in
northwestern Uganda. Its bases abroad were eliminated by Zairean
and Sudanese rebels recently. Its leaders were killed or captured
in last few days. The high court in Kampala has charged some of
its members with treason. enditem

