<HEADLINE> Helsinki Happy to Host U.S.-Russian Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The U.S.-Russian summit due to
be held in Helsinki, the capital of Finland, this week is a rare
opportunity for the country to draw world attention, local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
"It's a thousand times better than a public relations
brochure," Tuula Lindberg, head of the Helsinki Finland Congress
Bureau, was quoted as saying.
</P>
