<HEADLINE> Curb on Illegal Skin Exports Urged in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has been urged
to immediately put in a system to check rampant illegal exports of
game skins which have been going on unabated for a long time.
</P>
<P>
The appeal was made by a leather company's Managing Director Peter
Gross in Ndola, Copperbelt, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
A news dispatch from Ndola quoted Gross as saying that Zambia is
losing millions of Kwacha (1,300 kwach equal one US Dollar) in
foreign exchange every month through illegal exports of game skins to
Europe.
</P>
<P>
Most dealers have engaged local poachers who kill game
indiscriminately for meat and skins. The same skins are later brought
into Zambia as finished products and fetch away much money.
</P>
<P>
The illegal exports have greatly affected operations of the local
leather industry which is lacking vital raw materials for various
products.
</P>
<P>
Gross called for the screening of some game hunters who are
allegedly involved in the scourge to deprive the local leather
industry of raw materials. enditem

