<HEADLINE> Philippines Lists Products for Inclusion in ITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government has
included in its preliminary list about 60 products to be endorsed
under the Information Technology Agreement (ITA), the local press
reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The products listed were suggested by the participating sectors
during public hearings conducted by the Tariff Commission to
determine the scope and corresponding tariff rates under the ITA.
</P>
<P>
These products include computer hardware, software,
telecommunications equipment, semiconductor, manufacturing
equipment and other products.
</P>
<P>
The same list of products was also endorsed by the Philippine
government during a meeting of the World Trade Organization (WTO)
in Singapore last year.
</P>
<P>
A final list of products will be submitted to President Fidel
Ramos for final approval soon, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Under the ITA, tariffs for IT products shall be reduced to zero
starting January 1, 2000, as provided in the most favored nation
status of all WTO members.
</P>
<P>
Philippines tariffs for selected IT products are now at 3
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
