<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tensions High in East Jerusalem Over Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Tensions are continuing to
mount between the Israelis and the Palestinians over today's
projected start of construction at Har Homa in the Arab East
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The military authorities Monday night declared the Palestinian
areas from Bethlehem to Beit Sahur a "closed military zone", which
lies close to Har Homa in south Jerusalem. According to Israeli
law, without special permission anybody who enters the area will
run the risk of his life.
</P>
<P>
Army and police have also reinforced their deployment in
the West Bank in anticipation of violent Palestinian opposition
to the construction at Har homa.
</P>
<P>
At the construction site of Har Homa, army and police
units remain in standby in case of confrontation with
Palestinian protesters once the ground breaking begins.
</P>
<P>
On Monday night, Security forces threatened to remove the
protest tents set up by PLO Executive Committee Member Faisal
Husseini earlier in the day on the slope of a nearby hill
overlooking the Har Homa site.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu is due to hold a special
cabinet session to assess with relevant ministers and security
chiefs the situation in the Palestinian territories.
</P>
<P>
Surveyors are expected to arrive at Har Homa this morning
to begin charting the land for a squadron of bulldozers that
are standing ready nearby. The bulldozers will likely start work
afterwards. 
</P>
