<HEADLINE> Thai Police to Receive Midwifery Training </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government is launching
a program to have Thai traffic police receive midwifery training
to cope with the increasing chance of births on the road due to
the traffic jams.
</P>
<P>
Under the program jointly launched by the police authorities
and the Thai Red Cross Society, some 700 traffic police will
undergo the training.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Thai Red Cross Society said the program was
necessary for the safety of mothers and babies.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers said that in 1996, 72 mothers-to-be called for
help from the traffic police in Bangkok and four gave birth en
route to the hospital.  
