<HEADLINE> Cargo Handling Resumes at Bangladesh's Largest Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Dock workers at Bangladesh's
largest Chittagong Port have agreed to resume cargo handling today
following an agreement with the port authority, said reports
reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement reached Monday night, the port authority
will take steps to remove two forklifts of a private shipping
company from the protected area of the port.
</P>
<P>
Cargo handling at the seaport has been suspended since last
Saturday as the dock workers went on strike, demanding immediate
measures to stop the use of private cargo handling equipment at
the port.
</P>
<P>
Because of the strike, 21 ships loaded with tens of thousands
of cargo got stuck on the outer sea. Besides, 17 loaded ships were
waiting at the jetties for unloading.  
</P>
