<HEADLINE> East China Province to Improve Agriculture By Science </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Fujian province in east China is
set to use science and technology for agricultural upgrading
during the Ninth-Five-Year-Plan period (1996-2000), according to
Chen Mingyi, the top official in the province.
</P>
<P>
Chen says that the province will improve the combination of
agriculture, science, technology, and education and organize 200
experts and 10,000 technicians to go to rural areas to teach the
use of practical agricultural technology.
</P>
<P>
Attention will also be paid to technological progress in key
agricultural areas and to introducing high-quality crops and
breeding techniques from elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
A rural network will be established to spread the use of new
practical farming techniques and a scientific training system will
be improved to train 200,000 farmers this year.
</P>
<P>
The province has built the Shanming state-level demonstration
zone for combining agriculture, science and technology, and
education, and the Zhangzhou agricultural demonstration zone, as
well as nine provincial high-yield, high efficiency agricultural
demonstration zones. 
</P>
