<HEADLINE> Water In East China City Becomes Purer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Springs, pools, and streams at
scenic Hu Qiu (Tiger Hill) in east China's Suzhou city are limpid
once again thanks to a water purification project.
</P>
<P>
From the start of last year, engineering teams began building
an underground tunnel between "Third Spring," "Sword Pool," "White
Lotus Pool", and "the Crane Stream" to make it possible for water
to flow between them.
</P>
<P>
With the help of a water treatment system, water from Xishanwu
is purified before entering a river near the hill, and visitors
can hear the murmuring of streams that has been gone for decades.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
