<HEADLINE> Czech Social Democratic Party elects New Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Milos Zeman was re-elected
Chairman of the Czech Social Democratic Party at its Party
Congress that ended here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Zeman is now Chairman of the Czech Chamber of Deputies and his
Social Democratic Party (SDP) is the biggest opposition party in
the republic.
</P>
<P>
In the general election held in June 1996, the SDP got less
votes than the ruling Civil Democratic Party headed by Prime
Minister Vaclav Klaus.
</P>
<P>
The Social Democratic Party adopted a resolution at its
congress, strongly criticizing the policy of the present
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
