<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Port City Develops Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The port city of Lianyungang, the
eastern terminal of a rail that span through Asia to Europe, has
become a hot tourist site.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Lianyungang, one of the 49 major tourist cities of
China, received over 1.5 million Chinese and overseas tourists,
which generated tourist receipts of 980 million yuan (11.807
million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The city in east China's Jiangsu province is the starting point
of the railway, the "Eurasian Continental Bridge", which stretches
from China to Rotterdam.
</P>
<P>
Renowned tourist attractions of the city include the Yuntaishan
Scenic Area, primitive cliff carvings, and cliff Buddhist statues
of the Han Dynasty (206 BC- 220 AD) on the Wangkong Mountain.
</P>
<P>
According to city officials, a new highway linking Lianyungang
with Nanjing and the double-tracking of a railway trunk line
connecting with Lanzhou City, will enhance the city's edge in
developing tourism.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to tap the beach-side resources, including
turning Dongxilian Island into a holiday resort.
</P>
<P>
New tourist routes featuring historical sites, hot springs, and
folklore are being planned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
