<HEADLINE> Changbai Mountain Attracts ROK Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Capital from the Republic of
Korea (ROK) wakes up Changbai Mountain, at the Sino-Korean border,
to develop tourism.
</P>
<P>
Recently, seven contracts involving 245 million yuan (29.518
million US dollars) of investment and five letters of intent
valued at 27 million yuan were signed between Chinese and ROK
investors. They agreed to jointly invest in hotels, recreational
facilities, a ski resort, cable ways, and camping grounds around
the mountain.
</P>
<P>
The deals were struck between Antu county of Jilin province and
the Business Men Association of Kang Nam KU of Seoul.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that by this summer, 200 sets of tents and 2,000
eiderdown quilts funded by ROK investors will arrive.
</P>
<P>
A volcano landscape, with luxuriant primeval forests, an
elegant form of primitive, and beautiful mountain scenery, the
Changbai Mountain has become a major tourist attraction in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Antu county has decided to invest over two billion yuan to
build a tourist resort that embodies a ski resort, icicle flowers,
trails in the snow, a recreational park, a tour railway, an
exhibition center, and an international club.
</P>
<P>
Last year, over 110,000 overseas tourists went to the mountain,
most of them from ROK, Japan and southeast Asian countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
