<HEADLINE> China's PLA General Visits Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Italian Defense Chief of Staff Guido
Ventoroni gave a banquet this evening in honor of Fu Quanyou,
Chief of General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army,
who is paying a five-day official visit to Italy beginning today.
</P>
<P>
Ventoroni said at the banquet that both Italy and China have a
long history of civilization and a long standing friendly
relationship which has been further developed after the second
world war.
</P>
<P>
He said his visit to China in 1995 and Fu's visit to Italy
today are proofs of such friendship.
</P>
<P>
Fu said he agreed with Ventoroni's comments on the relations
between Italy and China and said his visit to Italy aims to
enhance the understanding, strengthen the friendship and promote
cooperation between the two nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
