<HEADLINE> East China Province Promotes Forest Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Shandong Province in east China is
speeding up the exploitation of its forest resources through
industrialization.
</P>
<P>
The building of forestry product bases has provided a material
foundation for the development of the province's forestry economy,
adding 10,000 ha of fast-growing forests in the past two years,
and 130,000 ha of economic forests and about 6,000 ha of flowers.
</P>
<P>
The province has a total forest area of 620,000 ha that
produces 10.5 billion kg of fruits.
</P>
<P>
Processing businesses are playing a key role in promoting the
industrialization and the province is paying closer attention to
establishing big processing enterprises, concentrating on apples,
pears, gingko, chestnuts, and flowers.
</P>
<P>
The provincial forestry department has spent 84 million yuan
(about 10 million US dollars) enhancing the processing industry
and has improved the establishment of markets. The number of
flower wholesale markets is now 113.
</P>
<P>
It has adopted a brand-name strategy, taking advantage of some
old brand-name products and developing a group of new ones, such
as the Anqiu peach and Qingzhou flowers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
