<HEADLINE> More Government-Subsidized Housing on Sale in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Different cities in Guangdong
province of south China are working hard to sell
government-subsidized flats as they accumulate public funds for
more housing construction.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the province had sold 55,000
government-subsidized flats, with a combined floor space of 3.85
million sq m, and collected 1.52 billion yuan from the sales.
</P>
<P>
Some 19 cities and 39 counties use a public accumulative
funding system for housing, with the participation of over 20,000
organizations and 1.9 million workers, which has helped pool 1.8
billion yuan into a special fund for housing.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Shenzhen, Shantou, Shanwei, Zhuhai, Jiangmen,
Zhanjiang and Shenzhen have been authorized to try the state's
"comfortable housing" program -- building apartments for urban
families with moderate and low income. They have pooled 850
million yuan for the purpose and have constructed 820,000 sq m of
economic flats.
</P>
<P>
Individual buyers, the main customers of the open housing
market, make up 70 percent of the total volume of the commercial
houses sold, according to local sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
