<HEADLINE> Investment Grows Fast in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 18 (Xinhua) -- Investments in fixed assets in
the Pudong New Area reportedly topped three billion yuan for the
first two months of this year, a rise of 94.1 percent over the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Local sources reported that among the investments nearly two
billion yuan went to capital construction, up 5.1 percent over the
comparable 1995 figure.
</P>
<P>
A group of major projects have been started in the region since
early this year, such as the Pudong International Airport and the
No. 2 Underground line.
</P>
<P>
And the proportion of investment from the central government
dropped from 61.8 percent to 40.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said that the target set for the Ninth
Five-Year Plan period (1996-2000) for capital construction
investment is approximately 100 billion yuan, four times the
amount during the Eighth Five-Year Plan period (1991-1995). 
</P>
</TEXT>
