<DOCNO> XIE19970318.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albanian Socialist Party Leader Urges Support for Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Socialist Party Chairman
Fatos Nano has called on all his countrymen to support the newly
formed national reconciliation government.
</P>
<P>
All parties including the Socialist party should give their
support to the new government to help restore order and peace, as
it is the key authoritative organ today that could make the
country return to normal, Nano told a news conference.
</P>
<P>
Nano also said that President Sali Berisha should resign.
</P>
<P>
"Since the majority of protesters continue to demand his
resignation it means he hasn't got the message. I would prefer to
shake hands with him as an Albanian citizen and not as president,"
said Nano.
</P>
<P>
Nano, who was sentenced for 12 years of imprisonment in 1993 on
alleged corruption charges, was amnestied by President Berisha
last week.
</P>
<P>
The Socialist chairman, briefly prime minister in 1991, is
considered the major challenger to Berisha. 
</P>
</TEXT>
