<HEADLINE> Argentine, French Presidents Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President Carlos
Menem said today his country's relations with France are excellent
and are at their highest level.
</P>
<P>
President Menem made the remarks during a ceremony at the
government palace welcoming French President Jacques Chirac, who
arrived here Sunday for a two-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
Menem expressed his faith in strengthening the relations
Between Argentina and France.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Chirac agreed with Menem that the two countries,
starting from their Latin origins, have a lot in common in
political, economic and cultural relations.
</P>
<P>
Then, the two presidents held their first working meeting to
discuss, among other topics, the outlook for French investments in
Argentina, the visit by a large business delegation from France,
and the international political situation in general.
</P>
<P>
Argentina is the last stop of Chirac's Latin America tour this
week, which has taken him to Brazil, Uruguay, Bolivia and Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
The visit aims to consolidate the relations between France and
the member countries of the South American Common Market
(Mercosur). 
</P>
