<HEADLINE> Mercosur Approves Creation of Inter-Regional Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Member states of South America's
biggest trade bloc Mercosur have agreed to create an
inter-regional bank, mainly to support infrastructure projects in
the region, Brazil's Ministry of Planning said today.
</P>
<P>
The planning and finance ministers of Argentina, Bolivia,
Brazil, Uruguay and Paraguay approved the operating rules for the
bank, to be known as Banco del Mercosur, on Sunday in Barcelona,
Spain.
</P>
<P>
The new bank will be primarily a development bank, similar to
other multilateral financial organizations such as the
Inter-American Development Bank (IDB).
</P>
<P>
IDB experts estimate that Mercosur's five members will need at
least 20 billion U.S. dollars of investment over the next few
years for infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
The IDB will contribute 200 million dollars to the Banco del
Mercosur's initial capital, the Brazilian ministry said. 
</P>
