<HEADLINE> Number of Refugees fleeing Albania to Italy to Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini said
today that authorities have noted "a certain improvement underway"
in the flow of Albanians fleeing their country for Italian shores.
</P>
<P>
Dini said Italy was committed to giving an "adequate reception"
to the refugees but "naturally we think the flow can be and
should be limited in time, that is, only temporarily."
</P>
<P>
A total of 5,621 Albanian refugees have arrived in Italy since
March 13, according to police figures released today. Among them,
1,012 are seeking asylum in Brindisi, 1,336 in Bari, 551 in Lecce,
with smaller numbers in other cities of Puglia and the Marches.
</P>
<P>
Some 120 air and sea-borne craft were used by the refugees,
including military helicopters and navy vessels. 
