<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Local Laws and Regulations Help South China's Market Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 18 (Xinhua) -- The legislature of China's island
province of Hainan has formulated 81 local laws and regulations
since the island became a special economic zone eight years ago.
</P>
<P>
The laws and regulations have helped form a legal framework
which facilitates the building of a socialist market economy,
according to officials with the Hainan Provincial People's
Congress.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the congress passed 20 laws and regulations on
gasoline tax, autonomy for the Li and Miao ethnic groups in
Baoting county, blood donations, and recruiting soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Approved by the National People's Congress, the Hainan People's
Congress has also adopted a regulation on law firms to link the
province with the regular international practice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
