<HEADLINE> Chinese Skaters Pass Figure Skating Qualifying Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, Switzerland, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Defending world
championship runner-up Chen Lu of China is among 30 skaters who
have passed the ladies' qualifying round at the 1997 World Figure
Skating Championships being held here in Lausanne from March 16 to
23.
</P>
<P>
Another Chinese Guo Zhengxin is among 30 men's skaters who
passed the qualifying round on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"Chen Lu has been having problems with her foot," said Chen's
coach Li Mingzhu. "She has only been training for three or four
weeks."
</P>
<P>
Li added that Chen's aim was to qualify for the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The first 24 skaters in the ladies' singles and the first 24
skaters in the men's singles will have the qualification to
compete in the 1998 Winter Olympic Games in Nagano, Japan.
