<HEADLINE> Airport Garden Square Built in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Gaoqi Airport in Xiamen, in east
China's Fujian Province, has completed the largest airport garden
square in China, covering an area of 86,000 sq m.
</P>
<P>
The airport built the largest airport lounge in the country
last year, and then decided to build the garden square on two
plots of land, which had originally been designated for a parking
lot and a commercial zone.
</P>
<P>
Various types of trees were planted in the square and two
five-tier flower beds are located along the sides of the square,
holding 1,200 pots of flowers. The square holds a total of 6,000
pots, with different seasonal flowers.
</P>
<P>
The airport has a total annual passenger volume of 3.6 million,
ranking seventh in the country. The square is intended to provide
the thousands of travelers with a more natural environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
