<HEADLINE> Thatcher Pledges Support for John Major </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Former British Prime Minister
Margaret Thatcher today urged voters to support his successor John
Major in the coming general election to be held on May 1.
</P>
<P>
The former Conservative Party leader was quoted by the BBC
television as saying this afternoon, "Stay with us and with John
Major until we cross the finish line."
</P>
<P>
She stressed that she would be fighting for the prime minister
"with every effort I can bring forth" during the election
campaign.
</P>
<P>
After announcing the polling day this morning, Major told a
gathering in Luton that the Conservatives would win the general
election and the British people would vote for the party which had
brought "a revolution in choice, opportunity and living
standards."
</P>
<P>
"We have the best economy we have had for generations and are
the envy of Europe," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
