<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief to Visit Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Secretary-General
Kofi Annan will start his four-day visit to Angola on Saturday,
U.N. special envoy Blondin Beye said here today.
</P>
<P>
Beye made the announcement in a press conference held after
talks with Roberto Da Almeida, speaker of the National Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Annan will address the swearing-in ceremony of the 70 members
of the National Assembly, said Beye who, however, failed to
disclose the date of the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
A total of 29 members have arrived in capital Luanda today to
assume their duties while the rest of MPs are coming "within the
next few hours", said Beye.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. envoy is expected to go to Bailundo on Thursday to
hold discussions with Jonas Savimbi, leader of the National Union
for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA), over some remaining
issues concerning the peace process. 
</P>
